The paper deals with finding lower bounds on the I/O complexity of computations, which involves analyzing the structure of computation graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), scientific computing (cs.SC), and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
